Opinion writers and commentators are praising President Trump's deal with Mexico to address the surge of migrants crossing the southern border. The deal involves Mexico taking greater action to reduce the flow of illegal immigrants into the United States. Critics have been proven wrong, and Trump is being praised for his achievement in getting Mexico to intensify the fight against illegal immigration. The deal is seen as a victory for national security and the rule of law. Trump's use of tariffs as leverage in negotiations is also being hailed as effective, with critics scrambling to contain his triumph. Overall, Trump is being commended for his decisive action and ability to get concrete results.